I"ù<p><a href="https://www.mkdocs.org">MkDocs</a> is a static site generator designed for building documentation websites.  Written in the Python programming language, MkDocs is an open-source project with a lot of community support. A variety of <a href="https://github.com/mkdocs/mkdocs/wiki/MkDocs-Themes">themes</a> are available. In terms of Markdown support, MkDocs does an excellent job supporting the basic syntax elements, but it lacks support for some extended syntax elements.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/tools/mkdocs.png" class="img-fluid" style="width: 70%;" alt="A newly deployed MkDocs site." /></p>

<h3 id="mkdocs-markdown-support">MkDocs Markdown Support</h3>

<p>MkDocs provides support for the following Markdown elements. The application uses the <a href="https://python-markdown.github.io/">Python-Markdown</a> Markdown processor. You can enable additional <a href="https://www.mkdocs.org/user-guide/configuration/#markdown_extensions">extensions</a>.</p>

